data.enText: to say nice things about sb, often in a way that is not sincere, because you want them to do sth for you or you want to please them
Are you trying to flatter me?
to choose to believe sth good about yourself and your abilities, especially when other people do not share this opinion

data.chText: “没有我看你怎么办？”“别自以为了不起。”
data.enText: ‘How will you manage without me?’ ‘Don't flatter yourself.’

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语 (+ that从句)

data.chText: 使显得更漂亮；使胜过本人
data.enText: to make sb seem more attractive or better than they really are

data.chText: 那种颜色很多人都不适宜。
data.enText: That colour doesn't flatter many people.

data.chText: 英格兰队在积分榜上的位置大大超过了其实力。
data.enText: The scoreline flattered England (= they did not deserve to get such a high score) .

data.chText: 被奉承得高兴；感到荣幸
data.enText: to be pleased because sb has made you feel important or special

data.chText: 她的关注使他感到格外高兴。
data.enText: He was flattered by her attention.

data.chText: 承蒙邀请来演讲，我深感荣幸。
data.enText: I felt flattered at being asked to give a lecture.

data.chText: 显得比实际好；看似比实际成功
data.enText: if sth flatters to deceive , it appears to be better, more successful, etc. than it really is

means: (尤指贴着另一表面)平直地，平躺地

ex.chText: 很明显，他只不过是在奉承苏珊。
ex.enText: It is obvious that he is just flattering Susan.

ex.chText: 称赞他的舞蹈就能讨好他。
ex.enText: You can flatter him by complimenting him on his dancing.

synonyms.bx: 指为了取悦某人或得到好处而赞扬某人，常含言不由衷之意。

ex.chText: 奉承我没用，我帮不了你什么忙。
ex.enText: It is no use buttering me up because I can do nothing to help you.
You can butter him up easily.

synonyms.bx: 指为了让别人帮自己做事而对其说好话。

ex.enText: He always sucks up to his manager.
She keeps sucking up to the teacher.

synonyms.bx: 指为了得到好处而取悦当权者，对其说很多好话或帮其做事，常后接介词 to。

ex.chText: 他是唯一一个得到奖金的人，因为他总是拍老板的马屁。
ex.enText: He is the only one that gets the bonus because he is always toadying to his boss.

ex.chText: 他们随后来到后台，对他奉承了一番。
ex.enText: They came backstage afterward and toadied to him.

synonyms.bx: 指为了能得到帮助而为有权势的人做事或假装对其欣赏、尊敬、友善等，常后接介词 to。

data.chText: 被奉承得高兴；感到荣幸
data.enText: to be pleased because sb has made you feel important or special

data.chText: 她的关注使他感到格外高兴。
data.enText: He was flattered by her attention.

data.chText: 承蒙邀请来演讲，我深感荣幸。
data.enText: I felt flattered at being asked to give a lecture.

data.chText: 显得比实际好；看似比实际成功
data.enText: if sth flatters to deceive , it appears to be better, more successful, etc. than it really is

value.def: If someone flatters you, they praise you in an exaggerated way that is not sincere, because they want to please you or to persuade you to do something.

example.ex: I knew she was just flattering me.
example.tran: 我知道她只是在恭维我。

example.ex: ...a story of how the president flattered and feted him into taking his side.
example.tran: 有关总统如何恭维并盛宴款待他、让他站到自己一边的故事

value.def: If you flatter yourself that something good is the case, you believe that it is true, although others may disagree. If someone says to you 'you're flattering yourself' or 'don't flatter yourself', they mean that they disagree with your good opinion of yourself.

example.ex: I flatter myself that this campaign will put an end to the war...
example.tran: 我自认为这次战役将结束这场战争。

example.ex: I flatter myself I've done it all rather well...
example.tran: 我认为自己已经做得相当好了。

example.ex: You flatter yourself. Why would we go to such ludicrous lengths?
example.tran: 你真自以为是。我们为什么要费那么大的力气?

value.def: If something flatters you, it makes you appear more attractive.

example.ex: Orange and khaki flatter those with golden skin tones...
example.tran: 橘黄色和卡其色能衬托那些金黄色皮肤的人。

example.ex: My philosophy of fashion is that I like to make clothes that flatter.
example.tran: 我的时尚理念就是我喜欢做让人穿着更显漂亮的衣服。
